<heading lvl="1">What is claimed is: </heading>

<claim id="CLM-00001">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>1</bold></highlight>. A glove to unload bony prominences of the hand comprising: 

<claim-text>a covering for said hand with separate elongated sections to receive a plurality of fingers therein, said covering having a top portion for covering a back side of the hand including a top side of said elongated sections to receive a plurality of fingers and a lower portion to cover a palm side of a hand including a bottom side of said elongated sections to receive said plurality of fingers; and, </claim-text>

<claim-text>at least one protective pad attached to the bottom portion of the covering below the center axis of rotation of a proximal interphalangeal joint of an index finger. </claim-text>

</claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00002">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>2</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> wherein said top portion includes elastic material in the vicinity of a human wrist to be received within said glove, said elastic material extending from the human wrist to an area adjacent each metacarpophalangeal joint of at least one finger. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00003">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>3</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> said bottom portion including elastic material adjacent a human wrist to be received within said glove. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00004">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>4</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference>, at least one of said elongated sections to receive a plurality of fingers including an upper portion of synthetic material. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00005">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>5</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> said lower portion having a second protective pad above the center axis of rotation of the proximal interphalangeal joint of said index finger. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00006">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>6</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00005"><claim-text>claim 5</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> including at least one protective pad below and at least one protective pad above the center axis of rotation of the proximal interphalangeal joint of each of said plurality of fingers. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00007">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>7</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference>, said elongated sections to receive a plurality of fingers therein including a section to receive a thumb, said section to receive a thumb including protective padding surrounding a distal phalanx, a metacarpophalangeal joint, metacarpal and carpometacarpal joint of said thumb. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00008">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>8</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00007"><claim-text>claim 7</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> wherein a proximal phalanx and an interphalangeal joint of said thumb is covered by two-way elastic material. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00009">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>9</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference>, said elongated sections to receive a plurality of fingers including a thumb element having elastic webbing material affixed laterally between said elongated sections beginning at a tip of an index finger to a section web at a junction along said hand where said index finger abuts a long finger and extends along a periphery of said elongated sections and terminates at a tip of a small finger. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00010">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>10</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> including an elastic band attached to said top portion and to said lower portion at a location above a human wrist section and at an opening into said glove. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00011">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>11</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> including protective padding affixed to said bottom portion to cover an area where a thumb contacts a palm. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00012">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>12</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> including thin elastic material attached to said upper portion covering a proximal interphalangeal joint, and a distal interphalangeal joint of each of said elongated sections. </claim-text>

</claim>

<claim id="CLM-00013">

<claim-text><highlight><bold>13</bold></highlight>. The glove of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> including thin elastic material attached to said lower portion to cover said proximal interphalangeal joint and said distal interphalangeal joint of each of said elongated sections. </claim-text>

