</claim>
<claim id="CLM-00008">
<claim-text><highlight><bold>8</bold></highlight>. The garment protector of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> wherein the protector cover includes at least two creases positioned below the first end of the protector cover and above the top of the pouch end extending substantially across the protector cover and positioned so that when the creases are bent the protector cover is retained in a shortened position and when the creases are straightened the protector cover is in a lengthened position. </claim-text>
</claim>
<claim id="CLM-00009">
<claim-text><highlight><bold>9</bold></highlight>. The garment protector of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> wherein the pouch is formed by positioning a plurality of folds in the sides of the pouch so that the pouch is foldable to a closed position with its bottom generally parallel to the front of the protector cover. </claim-text>
</claim>
<claim id="CLM-00010">
<claim-text><highlight><bold>10</bold></highlight>. The garment protector of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00009"><claim-text>claim 9</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> wherein the pouch also includes at least one fold across the front of the pouch. </claim-text>
</claim>
<claim id="CLM-00011">
<claim-text><highlight><bold>11</bold></highlight>. The garment protector of <dependent-claim-reference depends_on="CLM-00001"><claim-text>claim 1</claim-text></dependent-claim-reference> wherein a covered adhesive section is positioned inside and near the top of the front of the pouch so that when an adhesive cover is removed, the front and the back of the protector cover may be adhesively joined near the top of the pouch. </claim-text>
</claim>
<claim id="CLM-00012">
